e **stitch-flutter** skill.\n49\t\n50\t## Inputs\n51\t- `.stitch/designs/cycle-tracking/design.html` — HTML design mockup (written in Flutter HTML Glossary vocabulary)\n52\t- `.stitch/designs/cycle-tracking/SPEC.md` — Screen specification\n53\t- `.stitch/system/DESIGN.md` — Design system specification\n54\t\n55\t## How It Works\n56\t\n57\tThe HTML mockup uses the **Flutter HTML Glossary** — a constrained vocabulary where every HTML class and `data-*` attribute maps 1:1 to a Flutter widget. This enables mechanical, pixel-perfect conversion.\n58\t\n59\t## Conversion Steps\n60\t\n61\t1. **Read HTML** — Parse `.stitch/designs/cycle-tracking/design.html` and extract:\n62\t   - `:root` CSS tokens → update `lib/theme/app_theme.dart` if new tokens found\n63\t   - `.scaffold` element tree → this is the conversion entry point\n64\t   - `data-*` attributes → Flutter widget parameters\n65\t   - `data-animate` attributes → `flutter_animate` chains\n66\t   - `aria-*` attributes → `Semantics` widgets\n67\t\n68\t2. **Walk the DOM** — Process each glossary element top-down:\n69\t   - `.scaffold` → `Scaffold()`\n70\t   - `.app-bar` → `AppBar()`\n71\t   - `.column` → `Column()`\n72\t   - `.row` → `Row()`\n73\t   - `.card` → `Card()`\n74\t   - `.ink-well[data-route]` → `InkWell(onTap: () => context.push(route))`\n75\t   - `.network-image` → `CachedNetworkImage()`\n76\t   - `.icon[data-name]` → `Icon(Icons.{name})`\n77\t   - Text classes (`.title-large`, `.body-medium`, etc.) → `Text(..., style: textTheme.X)`\n78\t   - `data-color` → `colorScheme.X`\n79\t   - `data-spacing` → `AppTheme.spaceX`\n80\t   - `data-radius` → `AppTheme.radiusX`\n81\t\n82\t3. **Generate Dart** — Write `lib/screens/cycle_tracking/cycle_tracking_screen.dart`:\n83\t   ```dart\n84\t   import 'package:flutter/material.dart';\n85\t   import 'package:cached_network_image/cached_network_image.dart';\n86\t   import 'package:flutter_animate/flutter_animate.dart';\n87\t   import 'package:folio/theme/app_theme.dart';\n88\t\n89\t   class CycleTrackingScreen extends StatelessWidget {\n90\t     const CycleTrackingScreen({super.key});\n91\t\n92\t     @override\n93\t     Widget build(BuildContext context) {\n94\t       final theme = Theme.of(context);\n95\t       final colorScheme = theme.colorScheme;\n96\t       final textTheme = theme.textTheme;\n97\t\n98\t       return Scaffold(\n99\t         // ... mechanically converted from glossary elements\n100\t       );\n101\t     }\n102\t   }\n103\t   ```\n104\t\n105\t4. **Update router** — Add route to `lib/router/app_router.dart`:\n106\t   ```dart\n107\t   GoRoute(\n108\t     path: '/cycle-tracking',\n109\t     builder: (context, state) => const CycleTrackingScreen(),\n110\t   ),\n111\t   ```\n112\t\n113\t5. **Verify** — Run `dart analyze lib/screens/cycle_tracking/cycle_tracking_screen.dart`\n114\t\n115\t## Reference Skills\n116\t\n117\t- Read **flutter-building-layouts** for constraint rules (constraints down, sizes up), avoiding unbounded constraints in flex boxes, and when to use `Expanded` vs `Flexible` vs `SizedBox`.\n118\t- Read **flutter-animating-apps** for Hero transition setup, implicit vs explicit animations, and staggered animation patterns.\n119\t\n120\t## Quality Gates\n121\t\n122\t- **No hardcoded colors** — `Color(0xFF...)` and `Colors.blue` are banned; use `colorScheme.X`\n123\t- **No hardcoded text styles** — `TextStyle(fontSize: 16)` is banned; use `textTheme.X`\n124\t- **No hardcoded spacing** — `EdgeInsets.all(16)` is banned; use `AppTheme.spaceMd`\n125\t- **No Container abuse** — prefer `SizedBox`, `Padding`, `DecoratedBox` when Container is overkill\n126\t- **Use const** — `const` constructor wherever possible\n127\t- **Trailing commas** — on every parameter list\n128\t\n129\t## Success Criteria\n130\t\n131\t- `lib/screens/cycle_tracking/cycle_tracking_screen.dart` exists with valid Dart\n132\t- Uses `Theme.of(context)` for all styling (colors, text, shapes)\n133\t- No hardcoded colors, text styles, or spacing values\n